speaker: David Chen
text: Good morning everyone, thank you for joining this discovery call. I am David Chen, Head of Trade Finance Operations at ANZ Bank. We are looking to modernize our trade finance platform.

speaker: Ravikiran
text: Thank you David, great to meet you. I am Ravikiran from DXC Luxoft. We have extensive experience in trade finance modernization, having worked with CBA, SMBC, and several other major banks.

speaker: David Chen
text: That is impressive. Can you tell me about the CBA project? What was the team size and how long did the implementation take?

speaker: Ravikiran
text: For CBA, we deployed a team of 25 engineers over an 18-month period. The project achieved a 30 percent increase in processing efficiency and reduced manual intervention by 60 percent.

speaker: David Chen
text: That sounds excellent. We handle significant volumes of Letters of Credit and Bank Guarantees. How do you approach data privacy, particularly for regional data requirements in Asia Pacific?

speaker: Ravikiran
text: Data privacy is a top priority for us. We implement data residency controls at the platform level. For SCB in Singapore, we ensured all data stays within APAC data centers with full compliance to MAS guidelines.

speaker: David Chen
text: That is reassuring. Now, I understand you have AI capabilities in your platform. Is this AI currently in production or still in pilot phase?

speaker: Ravikiran
text: Our AI capabilities are fully in production at multiple client sites. We use machine learning for document classification, data extraction from trade documents, and anomaly detection for compliance. At OCBC, we achieved 95 percent accuracy in automated LC document processing.

speaker: David Chen
text: 95 percent accuracy is impressive. What about integration with existing core banking systems? We run a legacy mainframe for our back-office processing.

speaker: Ravikiran
text: Integration is our strength. We have pre-built adapters for major core banking platforms including Temenos, Finacle, and legacy mainframe systems. For CBA, we integrated with their AS400 system using our middleware layer with zero downtime.

speaker: David Chen
text: That addresses one of our major concerns. What would be the rough timeline for an implementation of this scope? We are looking at Letters of Credit, Bank Guarantees, and Supply Chain Finance modules.

speaker: Ravikiran
text: For that scope, we typically recommend a phased approach. Phase 1 would cover LC automation in about 6 months, followed by Bank Guarantees in another 4 months, and Supply Chain Finance in the final 6 months. Total implementation would be approximately 16 months.

speaker: David Chen
text: That timeline seems reasonable. Can you share some references we could speak with? Preferably banks in the Asia Pacific region.

speaker: Ravikiran
text: Absolutely. I can arrange reference calls with CBA Australia and SCB Singapore. Both have similar implementations and would be happy to share their experiences. I will send you the contact details after this call.

speaker: David Chen
text: Perfect. As next steps, I would like to schedule a technical deep dive with our IT architecture team next week. Can you also prepare a proposal with indicative pricing for our consideration?

speaker: Ravikiran
text: Certainly David. I will prepare a detailed proposal with three pricing options based on your scope requirements. I will also coordinate with our solutions architect for the technical session. What dates work best for your team?

speaker: David Chen
text: Let us aim for next Wednesday or Thursday. I will confirm by end of day tomorrow after checking with the team.

speaker: Ravikiran
text: Sounds great David. Thank you for your time today. I am excited about the opportunity to work with ANZ on this transformation. We will be in touch soon with the proposal and reference contacts.

speaker: David Chen
text: Thank you Ravikiran and the DXC Luxoft team. This was a very informative session. Looking forward to the next steps. Have a good day everyone.

text: Good morning! Thanks for taking the time to meet with us today. I'm David Chen, Head of Trade Finance Operations at ANZ Bank.

text: Good morning David, great to meet you. I'm Ravikiran from DXC Luxoft. We're excited to discuss how we can help modernize ANZ's trade finance operations.

speaker: Customer
text: Perfect. So tell me more about your trade finance solution and what makes DXC Luxoft different from other vendors we've spoken to.

speaker: Seller
text: Our platform provides end-to-end trade finance automation covering Letters of Credit, Bank Guarantees, and Documentary Collections. What sets us apart is our deep banking domain expertise combined with modern technology.

speaker: Customer
text: That's interesting. What about integration with existing systems? We have legacy core banking systems that we can't easily replace.

speaker: Seller
text: We support APIs for all major banking systems including Temenos, Finastra, and core SWIFT integration. Our modular architecture allows us to integrate without disrupting your existing infrastructure.

speaker: Customer
text: How long does implementation typically take? We've had bad experiences with vendors promising quick delivery but taking years.

speaker: Seller
text: Usually 12 to 18 months depending on complexity. For a bank your size with multiple product lines, I'd estimate 14-16 months for full implementation.

speaker: Customer
text: What was the team size for your last major project? And can you share some specific outcomes?

speaker: Seller
text: For CBA we had a 45-person team over 18 months. We achieved 30% reduction in processing times and 40% fewer manual errors. They now process over 50,000 transactions monthly.

speaker: Customer
text: That's impressive. What about other Australian banks? Have you worked with any of our competitors?

speaker: Seller
text: Yes, we've also worked with SMBC on LC automation where we integrated 3 core systems including SWIFT. They saw a 25% increase in straight-through processing rates.

speaker: Customer
text: That sounds reasonable. What about data privacy and regulatory compliance? This is a critical concern for us.

speaker: Seller
text: We follow strict regional data compliance requirements. For SCB in Singapore, we implemented data residency controls to meet MAS guidelines. All data stays within the specified jurisdiction.

speaker: Customer
text: How do you handle regional data sovereignty? We have operations across APAC and need to ensure compliance in each market.

speaker: Seller
text: Our platform supports multi-region deployment with data isolation. Each region can have its own data store while sharing business logic. We're certified for SOC 2 Type II and ISO 27001.

speaker: Customer
text: What about AI capabilities? We've been exploring how AI can help with document processing and fraud detection.

speaker: Seller
text: Great question. We have AI-powered document classification that achieved 92% accuracy in our POC with CBA. It handles trade documents like Bills of Lading, Invoices, and Certificates of Origin.

speaker: Customer
text: Is this AI actually in production or still experimental?

speaker: Seller
text: It's in production at two client sites. We use Azure OpenAI for document understanding and have built custom models for trade finance specific terminology and compliance checking.

speaker: Customer
text: What about pricing? Can you give me a ballpark figure for a project of our scale?

speaker: Seller
text: For a full implementation with your requirements, we're typically looking at 4 to 5 million dollars over the implementation period. This includes licensing, implementation services, and first year support.

speaker: Customer
text: That's within our budget range. What would you need from us to put together a formal proposal?

speaker: Seller
text: I'd need details on your current transaction volumes, the specific products you want to automate first, and your integration landscape. Could we schedule a technical deep-dive session next week?

speaker: Customer
text: Yes, let's do that. I'll have my team prepare the technical requirements document. Can you send over some case studies and your security documentation in the meantime?

speaker: Seller
text: Absolutely. I'll send those over today along with a high-level solution architecture. Thank you for your time today, David. I'm confident we can help ANZ achieve significant operational improvements.

speaker: Customer
text: Thank you Ravikiran. Looking forward to the next steps. Have a great day.
